# APM per-machine build output under ~/.apm. Only the contract (dot_apm/apm.yml)
# is managed; the lockfile and resolved packages are regenerated on each machine
# by run_onchange_after_apm-install (apm install -g). apm.lock.yaml is machine-
# specific (its deployed_files depend on which assistants are installed) and the
# pinned commit in apm.yml is the reproducibility anchor, so the lock is NOT
# committed. Defensive guards so a stray copy in the source dir is never pushed
# into ~ (e.g. after an accidental `chezmoi add ~/.apm/...`).
.apm/apm.lock.yaml
.apm/apm_modules
.apm/apm_modules/**

# Security-sensitive skills kept out of public dotfiles.
# npm-release contains GitHub App IDs, release automation details,
# and distribution scripts that are useful for attackers targeting the
# release pipeline. Keep it local-only.

# .claude/skills/apm-usage/**


# age private identity (NEVER commit). Defensive guard against an
# accidental `chezmoi add ~/.config/age/`; the key file lives only on
# the local machine and must be backed up out-of-band (1Password etc.).
.config/age/**

# SSH keys (NEVER commit). ~/.ssh/config is managed (private_dot_ssh/),
# but id_github etc. are restored out-of-band (1Password / old machine).
# Defensive guard against an accidental `chezmoi add ~/.ssh/...`.
.ssh/id_*
.ssh/*_gpg*
.ssh/google_compute*
.ssh/known_hosts*
.ssh/allowed_signers
.ssh/agent/**

